00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,727
of תפיסה אחת. Tfisa Achat. So let's keep on going. אמר ליה

745
00:37:07,727 --> 00:37:09,195
רב יימר בר שלמיא לאביי, Amar lei Rav Yeimar bar Shalmiya le-Abaye,

746
00:37:09,195 --> 00:37:11,543
so רב יימר בר שלמיא Rav Yeimar bar Shalmiya said to אביי:

747
00:37:11,250 --> 00:37:12,718
Abaye: שני אחים ומקפידין זה על זה מהו? Shenei Achim u-Makpidin Zeh

748
00:37:12,718 --> 00:37:13,598
al Zeh Mahu?

749
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:17,960
Let's say they do recognize one another, it's even a case where

750
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:21,720
they're, you know, known each other for life, they're two brothers, but

751
00:37:21,720 --> 00:37:24,660
they actually are having a little feud, they're מקפידין Makpidin one on

752
00:37:24,660 --> 00:37:27,540
the other, maybe specifically in the sense of that they don't share

753
00:37:27,540 --> 00:37:30,260
their food with one another, you know, they've got some fight going

754
00:37:30,260 --> 00:37:32,380
on and don't you dare touch my food.

755
00:37:33,780 --> 00:37:35,720
Can they eat together or not?

756
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:41,720
One bread and one meat. אמר ליה, Amar lei, he said to

757
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:43,405
him, very famous phrase: יאמרו כל הסריקין אסורין וסריקי בייטוס מותרין. Yomru

758
00:37:43,405 --> 00:37:44,915
Kol ha-Serikin Assurin ve-Serikei Baitos Mutarin.

759
00:37:46,020 --> 00:37:50,860
So this is a way of the גמרא, Gemara, a great phrase

760
00:37:50,860 --> 00:37:52,830
the גמרא Gemara uses to express its concept called לא פלוג. Lo

761
00:37:52,830 --> 00:37:56,740
Plug. We don't make distinctions. Meaning, we're not going to assess every

762
00:37:56,740 --> 00:38:00,420
single ruling based on the particular context and determine does it make

763
00:38:00,420 --> 00:38:02,700
sense in this context or not. We're going to have some formal

764
00:38:02,700 --> 00:38:05,620
rules and we're going to be consistent about them even if some

765
00:38:05,620 --> 00:38:09,340
cases don't exactly fit. So that's לא פלוג, Lo Plug, we don't

766
00:38:09,340 --> 00:38:13,314
make these types of distinctions. This came up because the גמרא Gemara

767
00:38:13,314 --> 00:38:16,500
says in the משנה Mishna says in פסחים Psachim that you cannot

768
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:20,254
make מצה Matzah which you basically cut designs into the מצה Matzah

769
00:38:20,254 --> 00:38:23,000
and make them particular shapes because the time it takes to cut

770
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,560
the designs when it's dough could lead to it rising before you

771
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:28,545
bake it. So there was this person בייטוס בן זונין Baitos ben

772
00:38:28,545 --> 00:38:31,080
Zonin who's an interesting character who comes up a few times in

773
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:34,340
ש"ס, Shas, and he had cookie cutters. And he wanted to know,

774
00:38:34,420 --> 00:38:36,440
how about me? Can I use my cookie cutters? It doesn't take

775
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:40,380
any time. So they basically said no. What? People will say all

776
00:38:40,380 --> 00:38:43,560
types of designs are forbidden and the designs of בייטוס Baitos are

777
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:47,740
permissible? So we cannot allow for these types of distinctions. Now one

778
00:38:47,740 --> 00:38:52,220
way of explaining that is that if we allow your case, other

779
00:38:52,220 --> 00:38:54,880
people will allow other cases which don't deserve to have an exception.

780
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,200
And that's one reason to keep rules, that if you make one

781
00:38:57,200 --> 00:39:00,600
exception then it'll just it'll open up the floodgates. The other reason

782
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:02,880
to keep it on the formal level is just because it's impossible

783
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:05,860
to create law if every case is being adjudged on its own

784
00:39:05,860 --> 00:39:09,000
merits and there's not a consistent type of a standard. So this

785
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,200
is the idea of לא פלוג. Lo Plug. So אביי Abaye said

786
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:16,460
we can make a basic distinction between strangers and non-strangers. Okay, that

787
00:39:16,460 --> 00:39:18,160
is, and then we're consistent with that.

788
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:23,120
But as soon as but we can't start saying within people that

789
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:26,240
aren't strangers, we're going to assess the degree of how friendly they

790
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:29,960
are with one another. That's way too contextual, that's not categorical, we

791
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:32,560
can't do that. So yes, even if they're having a fight, they

792
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:33,700
can't eat at the same table.

793
00:39:34,780 --> 00:39:37,500
Let's keep on going. ולטעמיך, u-le-Ta'amecha, he said back to him, and

794
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:39,900
this is always the question that's asked about the cases where we

795
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:43,160
do make exceptions to the לא פלוג Lo Plug rule, to not

796
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:46,120
making exceptions. So there's an exception to the rule that we don't

797
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:46,280
make

798
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:48,546
exceptions. הא דאמר רב אסי אמר רבי יוחנן, Ha de-Amar Rav Assi

799
00:39:48,546 --> 00:39:50,480
Amar Rabbi Yochanan, that which רב אסי Rav Assi says in the

800
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:52,380
name of רבי יוחנן: Rabbi Yochanan: מי שאין לו אלא חלוק אחד

801
00:39:52,380 --> 00:39:52,452
מותר לכבסו בחול המועד. Mi she-Ein lo Ela Chaluk Echad Mutar le-Chabso

802
00:39:52,452 --> 00:39:54,940
be-Chol ha-Moed. You can't do laundry on חול המועד, Chol ha-Moed, we

803
00:39:54,940 --> 00:39:57,020
want you to get it done before יום טוב, Yom Tov, either

804
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:58,480
because of an איסור מלאכה Issur Melacha of חול המועד Chol ha-Moed

805
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,927
or because we want you to come into the יום טוב... Yom

806
00:39:59,927 --> 00:40:03,920
Tov... looking nice. Let's say you only have one shirt. So you

807
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:06,160
did come into the יום טוב Yom Tov looking nice, but now

808
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:08,940
it's, but now it's all sweaty and dirty. Can you do laundry

809
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:12,120
on חול המועד? Chol Hamoed? So we actually do allow that person.

810
00:40:12,300 --> 00:40:15,320
Ah, we're making a distinction, here we're allowing, everybody else we're not

811
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:17,860
allowing. Aren't we afraid that that's going to open up the floodgates,

812
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,780
we're making distinctions?

813
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:23,261
So יאמרו Yomru why not say כל הציקן אסור וציקי בייתות מותרים,

814
00:40:21,500 --> 00:40:24,620
kol hatzikan assur vetzikei baytot mutarim, the same way what, we're going

815
00:40:24,620 --> 00:40:27,440
to allow your, your designs in your מצה matzah and not everybody

816
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:31,020
else's. So say here too. What, you know, how could we allow

817
00:40:31,020 --> 00:40:33,640
you to do your laundry and not everybody else? So if everybody

818
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,440
else is אסור assur you're also אסור. assur. So why here are

819
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:39,960
we making an exception if we never make exceptions? So אמר מר

820
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:41,867
בר רב אשי amar Mar bar Rav Ashi איזורו מוכיח עליו. izoro

821
00:40:41,867 --> 00:40:45,094
mochiach alav. No, the גמרא Gemara says there there's an answer. מר

822
00:40:45,094 --> 00:40:47,860
בר רב אשי Mar bar Rav Ashi says your איזור, izor, your

823
00:40:47,860 --> 00:40:52,860
belt, proves it. What does that mean? So רש"י Rashi says because

824
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:55,500
basically if you're doing your laundry, you're doing your laundry in your

825
00:40:55,500 --> 00:40:57,940
bare back. You had to strip off your shirt to do your

826
00:40:57,940 --> 00:41:00,840
laundry. So everybody sees you've taken off your shirt, you've taken off

827
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:04,160
your belt that held your shirt in place and everybody, it's self-evident

828
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:09,020
why you are allowed. So an exception that is very clear why

829
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:13,140
it's an exceptional case we might allow. But other types of situations

830
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:17,000
we will not. Okay. Now back to the point here about eating

831
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:17,780
on one table.

832
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:22,220
So תוספות Tosafot points out that since the גמרא Gemara uses the

833
00:41:22,220 --> 00:41:25,800
phrase כעין תפיסה אחת ke'ein tfisa achat like it's one bundle, meaning

834
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:28,080
that they know each other, although the גמרא Gemara only uses it

835
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:28,500
to say

836
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:34,260
that it allows for cases of strangers and doesn't allow when they

837
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:37,180
know one another, תוספות Tosafot says well maybe even when they know

838
00:41:37,180 --> 00:41:40,100
one another it has to be this idea of like one bundle.

839
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:43,620
And if there is some type of a separation between the two,

840
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:47,140
that's okay. And that leads to a discussion in the תוספות Tosafot

841
00:41:47,140 --> 00:41:49,160
and in the ראשונים Rishonim and the אחרונים Achronim about what types

842
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:52,320
of separations. There are two types of separations. One might be a

843
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:55,320
physical barrier that if I'm going to reach over my hand to

844
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:57,260
try to get a piece of your cheese or of your meat,

845
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:00,060
I'm going to bump into something and that'll stop me and then

846
00:42:00,060 --> 00:42:04,480
I'll remember. So that's an actual physical barrier. And that also really

847
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,000
makes it like we're at two separate tables because there's something physical

848
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,860
between us. Others say that anything that reminds me even if it's

849
00:42:10,860 --> 00:42:15,220
not physical could suffice. So therefore anything that's a difference, if there's

850
00:42:15,220 --> 00:42:17,940
some type of a special thing on the table that makes me

851
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:22,080
remember, or a simpler example is if it's on a mat. So

852
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:23,900
I will do this, I'm eating at a table and people are

853
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:27,680
eating different things, so I will put underneath what I'm eating a

854
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:30,240
piece of paper or some type of a placemat and everybody else

855
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:33,120
is eating directly off of the table. That means my eating is

856
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:35,960
different from their eating, that's some type of a סימן siman that

857
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:39,194
serves as a reminder. So this idea develops based on this phrase

858
00:42:39,194 --> 00:42:41,340
תפיסה אחת tfisa achat not in the גמרא, Gemara, but it becomes

859
00:42:41,340 --> 00:42:44,400
a nice way to allow more latitude in this idea of not

860
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:47,820
eating on the same table. I should mention that probably one of

861
00:42:47,820 --> 00:42:50,600
the things that sort of pushed it in this direction is we

862
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:53,700
have to understand that שולחן shulchan in the גמרא Gemara is not

863
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:55,960
the type of big table we all have that we all share.

864
00:42:56,420 --> 00:42:59,660
In the גמרא Gemara you're referring or in the משנה Mishnah like

865
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:03,260
they would eat in Rome, that individual trays would be brought in

866
00:43:03,260 --> 00:43:05,260
front of a person. And that was called a שולחן shulchan like

867
00:43:05,260 --> 00:43:07,240
we find in the משנה Mishnah in פסחים Psachim when they bring

868
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:09,700
the tray the שולחן shulchan in front of him that has the

869
00:43:09,700 --> 00:43:14,780
מצה matzah and and every and everything. So therefore to eat on

870
00:43:14,780 --> 00:43:18,500
the same שולחן, shulchan, you're eating really like one on top of

871
00:43:18,500 --> 00:43:22,060
the other, you're all both eating off of the same tray. Nowadays

872
00:43:22,060 --> 00:43:25,100
that we have a big table, there's much less of a sense

873
00:43:25,100 --> 00:43:28,900
that we're really eating together in that intense way and therefore some

874
00:43:28,900 --> 00:43:32,380
type of a separation whether a physical barrier or just a סימן

875
00:43:32,020 --> 00:43:35,500
siman could suffice and that actually is how we rule. So with

876
00:43:35,500 --> 00:43:38,940
that we will end today's דף daf and we will pick up

877
00:43:38,940 --> 00:43:40,960
with tomorrow's דף. daf.
